    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Ah, if your Python 3 executable is `/usr/bin/python`, the shebang will point to that. As far as I know, setuptools just uses the Python executable you run to install it. I think you can specify a `--executable` option if you want to override that behaviour.\n\nClosing since I don't think there's anything we need to - or can - do.\n"
